RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 1 1 1/16M Turf CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 18100. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs. Preference to horses with the most starts at Penn National since May 31st 2022. (If deemed in advisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MACKENZIE'S NOVVA was well rated two wide, made a three wide bid leaving the quarter pole, then had a long drive and prevailed late gamely to prove best. ICANDOTHAT was reserved early, split rivals at the half mile marker to move into contention entering the turn, made a four wide move leaving the quarter pole to vie for the lead, then had a long drive with the winner but was out-kicked. TWIST OF FAITH was well placed on the inside, eased out by the quarter pole and came three wide into the lane, angled out in the lane and had no kick, held show award. UPTOWNJACOB BROWN was settled back early two wide, made a wide move on the turn and came six wide into the lane and improved late to just miss the show award. FIFTH ELEMENT was settled back on the inside, three wide on the turn and came four wide into the lane and improved position late. HENDERSON pressed the pace and made a two wide bid on the turn but weakened in the drive. TERRIBLEIGH tracked the pace three wide and tired. FAST FREEZE KAZ was away alertly to set a pressured pace early while getting to the inside, then gave way by the quarter pole. VALENTIN C was reluctant to load, off a step slow, settled three wide and tired. GOOD FORTUNE was settled on the inside and stopped.
